               <floruit notBefore="1450" notAfter="1508">.<persName ref="PRS1848AmdaMi">ʾAmda Mikāʾel</persName>
                  was an influential political figure from the reign of <roleName type="title">ʾaṣe</roleName> <persName ref="PRS10626ZaraY">Zarʾa Yāʿǝqob</persName> 
                  to that of <roleName type="title">ʾaṣe</roleName><persName ref="PRS7481NaodA">Nāʿod (ʾAnbasā Baḍar)</persName>. 
                  He was appointed as <roleName type="title">malkaññā</roleName> by <roleName type="title">ʾaṣe</roleName> 
                  <persName ref="PRS10626ZaraY">Zarʾa Yāʿǝqob</persName> over all of <placeName ref="LOC3061Fataga">Faṭagār</placeName>.
                  <persName ref="PRS1848AmdaMi">ʾAmda Mikāʾel</persName> is most remembered for the role he played in determining the successors 
                  to <roleName type="title">ʾaṣe</roleName><persName ref="PRS2334BaedaM">Baʾǝda Māryām I</persName>,  
                  <roleName type="title">ʾaṣe</roleName><persName ref="PRS3874eskender">ʾƎskǝndǝr</persName>, 
                  <roleName type="title">ʾaṣe</roleName><persName ref="PRS1855Amdase">ʾAmda Ṣǝyon II</persName><roleName type="title">ʾaṣe</roleName>  
                 and <persName ref="PRS7481NaodA">Nāʿod (ʾAnbasā Baḍar)</persName>. </floruit>
          
               
               
